<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> LITHUANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poland To Cooperate in Environmental Protection </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poland To Cooperate in Environmental Protection </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3103214994 Warsaw PAP in English 2018 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3103214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, March 31 -- Polish Minister of 
Environmental Protection, Natural Resources and Forestry 
Stanislaw Zelichowski and General Director of the Department for 
Environmental Protection of Lithuania Evaldas Vebra signed in 
Vilnius on Thursday a plan of cooperation between the two 
ministries for the years 1994-1995. 
  The plan provides for cooperation in environment monitoring, 
environmental protection in border regions as well as control 
and counteracting illegal transborder transport of waste. 
  During his two day official visit, the Polish minister was 
received by Lithuanian Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius, held 
talks at the Ministry of Forestry and met with the main 
geologist of the Republic of Lithuania. 
  Asked during a press conference whether the two sides 
discussed the Ignalina nuclear power plant which posed threat to 
natural environment not only in Lithuania, the Polish minister 
said they spoke about possibilities of cooperation in all fields. 
  Zelichowski said Poland had a modern monitoring system which 
would make it possible to detect any danger two hours after a 
break-down in the power plant. 
  Vebra stressed the signed plan of cooperation provides for 
cooperation in radiation monitoring. 

</TEXT>

