<H3> <TI>   Toepfer Promises Return of Toxic Waste From Albania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Toepfer Promises Return of Toxic Waste From Albania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1103143094 Hamburg DPA in German 1305 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn -- Environment Minister Klaus Toepfer 
(Christian Democratic Union) has announced an overall solution 
for the approximately 380 tonnes of pesticide toxic waste from 
the former German Democratic Republic [GDR] that has been stored 
in Albania for nearly two years. As he stated at a news 
conference today, he will present a concluding report next week. 
At the Bundestag on Thursday [10 March], he indicated that the 
pesticides transported to Albania are to be returned to Germany 
"in a more or less legal way" and disposed of here. 
  However, the financial aspect of the operation has 
apparently 
not yet been settled. The Finance Ministry has not yet released 
the 1.4 million German marks [DM] needed to handle the toxic 
waste, which is mainly stored in a train of the GDR Railroads. 
The costs for the return and disposal are expected to be much 
higher. A similar operation during which waste from Romania was 
transported back to Germany involved about DM10 million. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

