  [Text] The Netherlands and Ukraine signed a "memorandum of 
understanding" on the subject of environmental protection on 
February 19 in the East Netherlands town of Amersfoort. This 
preliminary agreement received the signatures of Dutch 
Environment Minister Hans Alders and his Ukrainian opposite 
number MrKostenko. The main points covered in the memorandum of 
understanding are climate protection, as well as water and 
nature safeguards. Cooperation in these fields is expected to 
take the form of scientific and technical information exchange, 
exchanges of experts and holding conferences. 

