<H3> <TI>     Tokyo `Unable To Confirm' Perry Claims on DPRK Nuke Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo `Unable To Confirm' Perry Claims on DPRK Nuke Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0504140794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Apr 94 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM0504140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report from the "Yesterday, Today, and Tomorrow" </F>
column: "Does North Korea Have a Specific Program?"] 
  [Text] Tokyo is unable to confirm the statement by U.S. 
Secretary of Defense William Perry that the DPRK has started 
implementing a program which will enable it to produce at least 
twelve nuclear devices a year within two to three years. An 
ITAR-TASS correspondent was informed of this by a senior 
Japanese Foreign Ministry official. 
  He observed that he did not know the reasons which enabled 
the U.S. secretary of defense to make such a statement during an 
interview with a U.S. television company Sunday [3 April]. 

</TEXT>

