<H3> <TI>   Taihikai Members Hold ASAHI SHIMBUN Employees Hostage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Taihikai Members Hold ASAHI SHIMBUN Employees Hostage </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Gunmen Take 10 Hostages </H4>

<F P=102> OW0104053194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0515 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0104053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 1 KYODO -- Two gunmen entered the Tokyo 
headquarters of the national daily ASAHI SHIMBUN at about 1:30 
p.m. Friday [1 April] and took 10 of the company's employees 
hostage on the building's 15th floor, police said. 
  Police said the gunmen were right-wingers and were also 
armed 
with a sword and dynamite. Police said one of the men had fired 
a shot from a gun. 

