<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   31 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Revolutionary Movement Molotov Cocktail Attack Injures Nine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Revolutionary Movement Molotov Cocktail Attack Injures Nine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3103224894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1930 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA3103224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leon (Mexico), 31 Mar (EFE) -- Authorities reported 
today nine people were injured during a Molotov cocktail attack 
allegedly executed by members of the Leftist Revolutionary 
Movement (MIR) [Movimiento de Izquierda Revolucionaria] in Leon, 
Guanajuato, central Mexico. 
  The attack, which occurred yesterday afternoon, has left 
more 
than 50 people homeless, because it caused a fire that destroyed 
13 houses. 
  Local police reported the reasons for the incident are still 
undetermined, but witnesses say two men called Arturo Andrade 
and Rito Duran, MIR leaders, were the ones who threw the bombs. 
  Area residents have said this is not the first time the 
alleged culprits have attacked the area with explosives. Five 
years ago, the residents say, those people also threw bombs at 
them, because they refused to pay a cooperation quota to their 
organization. 
  The attack was apparently aimed against the house of Maria 
Guadalupe Perez, a former MIR member who decided to leave that 
organization a few months ago. 
  MIR is an ultra-leftist political organization that emerged 
in the past decade and has influence in several states in 
central Mexico. MIR has not openly declared itself an armed 
group. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

