<H3> <TI>   Update on Colosio Assassination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Update on Colosio Assassination </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Former Policeman Arrested for Complicity </H4>

<F P=102> PA2903192194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1807 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2903192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Mexico City, 29 Mar (EFE) -- Today the Attorney 
General's Office (PRG) accused former policeman Tranquilino 
Sanchez Venegas of complicity in the murder of Luis Donaldo 
Colosio. [passage omitted] 
  The suspicion that he participated is based on an analysis 
of 
the videotape broadcast on television and on graphic material in 
the Police's possession, where it appears that Sanchez Venegas 
opens a path for the murderer through the crowd while watching 
-- without acting to prevent -- as confessed murderer Mario 
Aburto Martinez shoots Colosio in the right temple. 
  Various PRG officials, who asked to remain anonymous, 
indicated that the arrest of the former policeman was made after 
a lady friend of Aburto Martinez declared that on 11 March the 
two individuals met in a Tijuana park. 
  According to official reports, the former policeman was 
employed by the Tijuana PRI for ``crowd control'' at the event 
were Colosio was murdered. [passage omitted] 
  The PRG has indicated that for now no one else has been 
arrested as an accomplice in the murder, although several 
individuals are being investigated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

