BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tarapoto -- It has been reported here that former 
Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement (MRTA) militants have made 
known the location of a common grave in Yurimangas that was dug 
by the movement's leaders. 
  The clandestine cemetery is 40 km south of Yurimangas. It is 
believed to contain the remains of MRTA members who died in 
confrontations with the forces of order. 
  It is also understood that the grave contains the victims of 
the MRTA's subversive insanity who, after being captured, were 
murdered without pity and their bodies thrown into the common 
grave. [passage omitted] 

