<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   31 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Qadhdhafi Meets Palestinian Alliance Force, Offers Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Qadhdhafi Meets Palestinian Alliance Force, Offers Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Libya Promises Financial Aid </H4>

<F P=102> JN3103173794 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 31 Mar 94 p 26 </F>
<F P=103> JN3103173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] QUDS PRESS--A senior official of the Palestinian 
organization Hamas, which opposes peace negotiations with 
Israel, has said that Libya has promised the Alliance of 
Palestinian Forces [APF] financial and political aid for the 
liberation of Palestine. 
  Ibrahim Ghawshah, official spokesman for Hamas, the biggest 
faction within the APF, said that a delegation of all the 
leaders from the opposition factions recently returned from an 
official visit to the Libyan capital Tripoli. He added that 
this is the first visit of its kind. 
  In a statement to QUDS PRESS, Ghawshah said that the leaders 
of the alliance visited Libya at the invitation of Libyan 
President Mu'ammar Qadhdhafi. He noted that the delegation 
included George Habash, secretary general of the Popular Front 
for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP]; Colonel Muhammad Musa, 
alias Abu-Musa, secretary of the central committee of the 
Palestine National Liberation Movement, Fatah-The Uprising; Dr. 
Fathi al-Shaqaqi, leader of the Islamic Jihad Movement; Talal 
Naji, assistant secretary general of the PFLP-General Command; 
'Arabi 'Awwad, secretary general of the Revolutionary Communist 
Party; Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general of the Democratic 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP]; 'Isam al-Qadi 
[secretary general of the Popular Liberation War Vanguards 
Organization-Al-Sa'iqah]; Abu-Nidal al-Ashqar [member of the 
Palestine Liberation Front Political Bureau]; Khalid 
'Abd-al-Majid [secretary general of the splinter group 
Palestinian Popular Struggle Front]; in addition to Ghawshah 
himself and Khalid Mash'al from Hamas. 
  The spokesman said that the delegation held a two-hour 
meeting with leader Qadhdhafi in Surt. The delegation demanded 
that Qadhdhafi support the intifadah and the mujahidin and work 
on stopping attempts of normalization with the Zionist enemy, as 
he said he would. The Palestinian official said that last 
Saturday, the delegation met with Colonel Abu-Bakr Yunus, the 
Libyan Chief of Staff and member of the ruling Revolution 
Command Council. 
  Ghawshah described the visit as useful and fruitful. He 
said: It is a gain in itself to exchange views and agree on 
common denominators dealing with Arab and official interests. 
He noted that Libya promised to offer more moral and financial 
support for the liberation of Palestine. He added that he 
expects the APF leadership to visit Iran on a date that has not 
yet been fixed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

