<H3> <TI>   Court Sentences Eight To Death In Absentia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Sentences Eight To Death In Absentia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104082694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0600 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0104082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At its session on 28 March, the special court of 
Algiers judicial council passed eight death sentences in 
absentia and another sentence of eight years imprisonment 
against an armed group of nine members on charges of forming and 
belonging to an armed group that aims at infringing on state 
security, killing, spreading sabotage, and premeditated murder. 
  According to a statement issued by the special judicial 
prosecutor, the details of the case followed the investigation 
and interrogation of one member of the group who was arrested. 
This is Sedrat Rabih, whose involvement in this group was 
proved. 
  He revealed that he used to collect and coordinate 
information in the region surrounding Boudouaou, and steal 
rifles from citizens. He assassinated three policemen in Hey 850 
Maskan in Boudouaou. 

</TEXT>

