</HEADER>

<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   29 March 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> ALGERIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Embassy Employee Killed South of Algiers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Embassy Employee Killed South of Algiers </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radio Names Assassins </H4>

<F P=102> LD2903233994 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903233994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following a series of investigations, the security 
services reveal the identity of a number of the executors of the 
Saoula operation, which targeted a Russian national. 
  Through the investigations opened by the security services 
on 
the assassination of a Russian national yesterday in Saoula, 
south of the capital, it became clear that the Russian national 
used to frequent a spare-parts merchant and an ironmonger in the 
area. 
  The same sources pointed out that the victim had made an 
application to the two merchants to buy certain products 10 days 
earlier and arrived at the specified time in the same car he was 
using to receive the merchandise. This gave his assassins a 
chance to seize him, then assassinate him. 
  The same sources said that the security services, which 
immediately surrounded the place after they were informed of the 
operation, succeeded in killing and identifying four of the six 
armed members. The matter concerns Seddou Said, Chalmouh Ahmed, 
and Boutiche Yazid, who lived in Ouled Fayek and Douira [only 
three names as received]. 
  The two armed persons sought out by the security services 
are 
Kisoume Omar and Zitouni Djamal. 
  The security sources reported that the search is still under 
way for Sayeh Atia, the main executor of the assassination of 
the governor of Tissemsilt and members of the accompanying 
delegation on 11 January last. 

</TEXT>

