<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Kill Suspected Informer in Asyut </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Kill Suspected Informer in Asyut </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2703194394 Paris AFP in English 1917 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2703194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Egypt, March 27 (AFP) -- Four gunmen believed 
to be Islamic militants shot dead a suspected police informer on 
Sunday at his shop in the troubled town of Asyut in southern 
Egypt, security officials said. 
  'Abd-al-Hafiz 'Abd-al-Na'im, 35, died on the way to 
hospital. 
  The officials said the outlawed Moslem fundamentalist 
organisation al-Jama'ah al-Islamiyah (Islamic Group) suspected 
'Abd-al-Na'im of informing police about its operations. 
  'Abd-al-Na'im's death raised to 53 the number of civilians 
killed since Islamic militants launched their violent 
anti-government campaign two years ago. The campaign has 
claimed a total of more than 300 lives. 

</TEXT>

