<H3> <TI>   Troops `Confiscate' Settlers' Weapons at Cave of Patriarchs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Troops `Confiscate' Settlers' Weapons at Cave of Patriarchs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2603131994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 26 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2603131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon, the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
prevented Jewish worshipers from Hebron from entering the Cave 
of the Patriarchs. 
  An Army source told our correspondent Moti Amir that the 
settlers caused a disturbance at the site and that the soldiers 
were forced to confiscate the weapons of some of the Jews in 
order to prevent a worse confrontation between them, the IDF, 
and Arab residents. No one was arrested but the soldiers took 
down the particulars of some of the settlers. 

