<H3> <TI>   Israeli Held for Killing Arab </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Held for Killing Arab </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2503193294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 25 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2503193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The police detained an Israeli citizen on suspicion 
that he had murdered an Arab truck driver, Riyad Salimi, from 
the village of Idnah in the Hebron area. He fired at him from 
an ambush at the Bet Guvrin junction, critically wounding him. 
The truck driver died at the Ashqelon Barzilay Hospital. Our 
correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that immediately after the 
shots the police erected roadblocks and launched searches. 
About 30 minutes after the incident, an unknown person called 
the Qiryat Gat police station and told the police how to capture 
the shooter. Following this person's instructions, the 
policemen detained a 42-year-old Israeli who was found in 
possession of an Uzi submachine gun and nine magazines. From 
his interrogation it was learned that the suspect fired many 
bullets at the truck. Our correspondent adds that it is 
believed he might have wanted to avenge the death of his brother 
who served in the Border Police in the Hebron area. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

