  [Excerpt] ``We are willing to suspend all combat operations 
under the supervision of international organizations and start 
talks with the Turkish authorities. But if the Turkish 
authorities refuse to come to the negotiating table, if the 
genocide against the Kurdish population continues, we will 
continue the struggle,'' Jamal Qadir, a spokesman for the 
National Liberation Front of Kurdistan [NLFK], said at a press 
