<H3> <TI>   Four RAF Members Reportedly Escaped in Bad Kleinen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four RAF Members Reportedly Escaped in Bad Kleinen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104091894 Hamburg DPA in German 0449 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DPA) -- According to the news magazine 
FOCUS, four RAF [Red Army Faction] members obviously escaped the 
police during the operation in Bad Kleinen. It is said that two 
so far unidentified persons -- a man and a woman -- whom police 
filmed in Bad Kleinen on 24 June, are two suspected terrorists. 
Police meanwhile assume that the couple was involved in the 
assassination of Trust Agency chief Detlef Karsten Rohwedder on 
1 April 1991. The magazine points to an internal paper of the 
Federal Office of Criminal Investigations [BKA], according to 
which the man might be the unknown person who was seen during 
the attack on Rohwedder. 
  A few hours before the operation on 27 June, police filmed 
another couple with a hidden camera in Bad Kleinen. BKA experts 
realized only later that these two people were suspected RAF 
members Daniela Klette and Ernst-Volker Staub. 

</TEXT>

