BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn -- Security near the Israeli Embassy in 
Bonn was further increased on Wednesday. In the afternoon, cars 
using roads near the embassy were checked very thoroughly. It 
seems that several locations were chosen where a great number of 
police have been posted. [passage omitted] 
  According to police, stepped-up security is to be in force 
over the next three to four days. After that, these activities 
will not be stopped altogether but decreased to a ``normal 
level.'' An Embassy spokeswoman said that security standards 
are very high, anyway. 

