<F P=102>   NC3003130794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3003130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to an ATHENS NEWS AGENCY dispatch, the 
Orthodox Patriarch's quarters at Fanari in Istanbul was attacked 
last night with two Molotov cocktails. According to the 
dispatch, at 2200 [1900 GMT] last night, unidentified people 
threw the two Molotov cocktails from the northern wall into the 
yard between the central building and library. Patriarch 
employees dealt with the fire before it caused any extensive 
damage. The fire department did not need to intervene. Turkish 
police are investigating the case. Similar incidents have 
occurred at least four times in the past couple of months but no 
effective safety measures have been taken at the Patriarch's 
quarters. 

</TEXT>

