<H3> <TI>   One Killed, Two Injured in Vitoria Bomb Blast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    One Killed, Two Injured in Vitoria Bomb Blast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2903071694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0800 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903071694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] One person died and another two were slightly 
injured last night in Vitoria when a bomb went off in the city 
center. The blast also caused substantial material damage in 
the area. The civil government has confirmed that the deceased 
is a young man who was carrying the device. Maria Jesus 
Iparaguirre is at the scene: 
  [Iparaguirre] [Passage omitted] The area is still cordonned 
off and the remains of the body, somebody who apparently was 
carrying or handling the device, are still here. According to 
Cesar Milano, the civil governor and the acting governmant 
delegate, the device could have comprised 15 or 20 kilos of 
amonal or amosal and shrapnel. Therefore, the target could have 
been a member of the state security forces. The incident took 
place at around 0520. [passage omitted] About 20 cars and 60 
dwellings have been affected. This is a shopping area and many 
shops have had their windows and interiors completely destroyed. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

