<H3> <TI>   Fourteen Killed in Explosion in Southeast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fourteen Killed in Explosion in Southeast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2703163294 Paris AFP in English 1457 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2703163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Turkey, March 27 (AFP) -- Fourteen 
people were killed and over 20 injured in an explosion in the 
village of Kocagili in south-eastern Turkey, well-informed 
sources in the regional capital of Diyarbakir said on Sunday [27 
March]. 
  According to injured survivors in Diyarbakir hospital, the 
village was attacked on Saturday by fighter planes of the 
Turkish airforce. 
  But authorities in the region denied this version of events, 
saying instead that a minibus had hit a mine near the village. 
  Also in Diyarbakir, a grenade was thrown at a school being 
used as a polling station in Sunday's municipal elections, 
slightly injuring two people. 
  By close of polls at 4:00 PM (1300 GMT), this was the only 
violent incident in the city directly linked to the elections 
despite threats against voters by Kurdish separatists. 

</TEXT>

